
[1]marigold

   MAR'IGOLD, n. A plant of the genus Calendula, bearing a yellow flower.
   There are several plants of different genera bearing this name; as the
   African marigold, of the genus Tagetes; corn-marigold, of the genus
   Chrysanthemum; fig-marigold, of the genus Mesembryanthemum;
   marsh-marigold, of the genus Caltha.
